cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC 

The paper deals with the decidability of language equivalence for deterministic pushdown automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses first-order grammars, which are a type of formal grammar, suggesting cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity analysis, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper deals with decidability, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, suggesting cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category.
